column4:
The National Institute for Health and Welfare (THL) has been carrying out regularly three national surveys (Health behaviour and health among Finnish adult population survey, FINRISK-survey and School Health survey) that include several questions on tobacco use, passive smoking and cessation. The surveys have constantly been developed, and now they include also information on e.g. tobacco dependence. THL has also participated in European School Survey Project on Alcohol and Other Drugs (ESPAD) -study since the beginning.  GYTS -study was carried out first time in 2013.
Finnish Tobacco Act has obligated THL and the Regional State Administrative Agency in cooperation with it to: 
1) be responsible for the nation-wide and regional action to reduce smoking; 
2) provide other State authorities and local authorities with health education programmes and other material on the dangers and harms to health originating from smoking; 
3) issue instructions aimed in particular at persons working with children and young people, health care professionals, public figures, employers and mass-media journalists on recommendable methods for avoiding and reducing smoking.

